TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi sealed PartialParseResult extends System.Enum

Docs.summary: The result of attempting an incremental parse
Docs.remarks: Either the Accepted or Rejected flag is ALWAYS set. Additionally, Provisional may be set with Accepted and SpanContextChanged may be set with Rejected. Provisional may NOT be set with Rejected and SpanContextChanged may NOT be set with Accepted.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.PartialParseResult Accepted = int32(2)

Docs.summary: Indicates that the edit was accepted and has been added to the parse tree

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.PartialParseResult AutoCompleteBlock = int32(16)

Docs.summary: Indicates that the edit requires an auto completion to occur

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.PartialParseResult Provisional = int32(4)

Docs.summary: Indicates that the edit was accepted, but that a reparse should be forced when idle time is available since the edit may be misclassified
Docs.remarks: This generally occurs when a "." is typed in an Implicit Expression, since editors require that this be assigned to Code in order to properly support features like IntelliSense. However, if no further edits occur following the ".", it should be treated as Markup.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.PartialParseResult Rejected = int32(1)

Docs.summary: Indicates that the edit could not be accepted and that a reparse is underway.

MemberSignature.Value: .field public static literal valuetype Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.PartialParseResult SpanContextChanged = int32(8)

Docs.summary: Indicates that the edit caused a change in the span's context and that if any statement completions were active prior to starting this partial parse, they should be reinitialized.
